.el .ds Aq '
.TH rom-weaver-patch-create 1  "rom-weaver-patch-create "
.SH NAME
rom\-weaver\-patch\-create \- Create a patch from original and modified ROM data
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBrom\-weaver patch create\fR [\fB\-\-json\fR] <\fB\-\-original\fR> [\fB\-\-modified\fR] [\fB\-\-progress\fR] [\fB\-\-format\fR] [\fB\-\-no\-progress\fR] [\fB\-\-output\fR] [\fB\-\-trace\fR] [\fB\-\-dep\-trace\fR] [\fB\-\-plan\fR] [\fB\-\-ignore\-checksum\-validation\fR] [\fB\-\-checksum\-name\fR] [\fB\-\-source\-crc32\fR] [\fB\-\-code\fR] [\fB\-\-code\-system\fR] [\fB\-\-code\-kind\fR] [\fB\-\-threads\fR] [\fB\-\-xdelta\-secondary\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Create a patch from original and modified ROM data
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-json\fR
Emit progress and terminal status as JSON lines
.TP
\fB\-\-original\fR \fI<PATH>\fR
Original ROM from which to create the patch
.TP
\fB\-\-modified\fR \fI<MODIFIED>\fR
Modified ROM to diff against the original. Optional when \-\-code is used; the modified ROM is then derived by baking the cheat codes into the original.
.TP
\fB\-\-progress\fR
Force running progress events on
.TP
\fB\-\-format\fR \fI<FORMAT>\fR
Patch format (derived from the output extension when omitted; required when the output has no recognizable patch extension)
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-progress\fR
Disable running progress events
.TP
\fB\-\-output\fR \fI<PATH>\fR
Output patch path; optional only with \-\-plan
.TP
\fB\-\-trace\fR
Enable trace logs (also enabled by ROM_WEAVER_LOG or RUST_LOG)
.TP
\fB\-\-dep\-trace\fR
Enable trace logs from dependencies (for example nod)
.TP
\fB\-\-plan\fR
Only return recommended formats; do not create a patch
.TP
\fB\-\-ignore\-checksum\-validation\fR
Skip strict patch validation during patch create when supported, including checksum emission and compatibility checks
.TP
\fB\-\-checksum\-name\fR
Embed the original ROM crc32 into the output patch file name (as `[crc32:HEX]`) so patch apply can validate the input ROM; most useful for formats that carry no embedded checksum
.TP
\fB\-\-source\-crc32\fR \fI<SOURCE_CRC32>\fR
Precomputed crc32 (8 hex digits) of the original ROM; used with \-\-checksum\-name to embed the value without re\-reading the original
.TP
\fB\-\-code\fR \fI<CODES>\fR
Cheat code (Game Genie or Pro Action Replay/GameShark) to bake into the original ROM to derive the modified ROM; repeat \-\-code for each. Mutually exclusive with \-\-modified.
.TP
\fB\-\-code\-system\fR \fI<CODE_SYSTEM>\fR
Override the cheat\-code system (nes, snes, genesis, gameboy) when it cannot be auto\-detected from the ROM header
.TP
\fB\-\-code\-kind\fR \fI<CODE_KIND>\fR [default: auto]
Cheat code scheme: auto (infer), game\-genie, or gameshark/par
.TP
\fB\-\-threads\fR \fI<auto|N>\fR [default: auto]
Thread budget: auto or a positive integer
.TP
\fB\-\-xdelta\-secondary\fR \fI<XDELTA_SECONDARY>\fR [default: none]
xdelta secondary compression mode during patch create (default none = no in\-patch compression, matching xdelta3 without \-S; lzma adds LZMA like xdelta \-S lzma; djw/fgk are xdelta3\*(Aqs huffman coders; auto compares djw/lzma/fgk and keeps the smallest)
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
auto
.IP \(bu 2
lzma
.IP \(bu 2
djw
.IP \(bu 2
fgk
.IP \(bu 2
none
.RE
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
